This topic highlights new features included in Pivotal Cloud Foundry (PCF) v1.11.

## <a id='om'></a>Ops Manager Highlights

Ops Manager v1.11 includes the following features:

- **NSX Security Group Integration**: Operators can configure Ops Manager v1.11 to communicate with VMware NSX. For more information,
see Step 5 in the [Configuring Ops Manager Director for VMware vSphere](../customizing/vsphere-config.html#vcenter-config) topic.
- **CredHub Integration**: CredHub centralizes and secures credential generation, storage, lifecycle management, and access. 
For more information, see our [CredHub](http://docs-pcf-staging.cfapps.io/pivotalcf/1-11/credhub/index.html) topics.
- **Syslog transport for BOSH Director logs**: Ops Manager v1.11 enables operators to send BOSH Director syslogs to a remote server. For more information,
see the Ops Manager Director configuration topic for your IaaS:
  - [Configuring Ops Manager Director on AWS](../customizing/cloudform-om-config.html#syslog)
  - [Configuring Ops Manager Director on Azure](../customizing/azure-om-config.html#syslog)
  - [Configuring Ops Manager Director on GCP](../customizing/gcp-om-config.html#syslog)
  - [Configuring Ops Manager Director for OpenStack](../customizing/cloudform-om-config.html#syslog)
  - [Configuring Ops Manager Director for VMware vSphere](../customizing/vsphere-config.html#syslog)
- Ops Mgr User Interaction Logging
- Support for Azure Managed Disks
- Secured BOSH Metrics Paths
- **Ops Manager VM hardening**: Ops Manager v1.11 inherits the security configuration of its stemcell. For more information about stemcell hardening,
see the [Stemcell Hardening FAQ](../security/pcf-infrastructure/stemcell-hardening.html) topic.
- Apply changes to BOSH Director only
- Improved collection of logs from multiple VMs

For more information, see the [Pivotal Cloud Foundry Ops Manager v1.11 Release Notes](../pcf-release-notes/opsmanager-rn.html).

## <a id='ert'></a>Elastic Runtime Highlights

Elastic Runtime v1.11 includes the following features:

- **Container to Container Networking**: Container to Container Networking is generally available in ERT v1.11. 
For more information, see the [Administering Container-to-Container Networking](../devguide/deploy-apps/cf-networking.html) topic.
- **NFS v3 Volume Services**: NFS v3 Volume Services is generally available in ERT v1.11. Additionally, Elastic Runtime ships with an NFS Volume Service Broker. For more information, see the [Using an External File System (Volume Services)](../devguide/services/using-vol-services.html) and [Enabling NFS Volume Services](../opsguide/enable-vol-services.html) topics.
- Intermediate retention of larger SCDF datasets
- UAADB and CCDB migration from PostgreSQL to MySQL
- SHA2 checksums
- **Private Docker Repositories**: ERT v1.11 enables developers to push Docker images from private registries that require authentication. For more information, see the [Push a Docker Image with Authentication](../opsguide/docker-registry.html#docker-auth) section of the <em>Using Docker Registries</em> topic.
- App syslog drain improvements
- TLS-based syslog of component logs
- **ERT defaults to highly available configuration**: In PCF v1.11 and later, Elastic Runtime defaults to a highly available resource configuration. However, you may need to complete additional procedures to make your deployment highly available. For more information, see the topic on configuring Elastic Runtime for your IaaS.
- Mutual auth and encryption of intra-component communication
- Java Buildpack 4.0

For more information, see the [Pivotal Elastic Runtime v1.11 Release Notes](../pcf-release-notes/runtime-rn.html).

## <a id='apps-man'></a>Apps Manager Highlights

Apps Manager v1.11 includes the following features:

* **Spring Actuator**: Apps Manager v1.11 includes Spring Actuator heap dumps, request traces, and thread dumps. For more information, see the [Using Spring Boot Actuators with Apps Manager](../console/using-actuators.html)
* **App Search**: You can now search for apps across all orgs and spaces by entering the name of the app in the search bar.
- **Route Services**: You can now manage route services from Apps Manager. For more information, see the [Manage Route Services](../console/manage-apps.html#manage-route-services) section of the <em>Managing Apps and Service Instances Using Apps Manager</em> topic.
- **Custom Health Checks**: You can now view custom application health checks in Apps Manager. For more information, see the [View Health Checks](../console/manage-apps.html#health-checks) section of the <em>Managing Apps and Service Instances Using Apps Manager</em> topic.
- **Tasks in the Usage Report**: The Usage Report now includes information about task usage. For more information, see the [View the Usage Report](../opsguide/accounting-report-apps-man.html#usage-report) section of the <em>Monitoring Instance Usage with Apps Manager</em> topic.
- **Last login notice**: Apps Manager v1.11 displays the date and time of the last login in the bottom right of the footer.
- **Section 508a compliance improvements**: Apps Manager has improved its compliance with [Section 508](https://www.section508.gov/) of the Rehabilitation Act. Customers can now receive an approved Voluntary Product Accessibility Template (VPAT) for Apps Manager.

For more information, see the [Pivotal Elastic Runtime v1.11 Release Notes](../pcf-release-notes/runtime-rn.html).

## <a id='pcf-is'></a>PCF Isolation Segment Highlights

The PCF Isolation Segment v1.11 tile includes the following features:

- **Sharded Routers**: Operators can now configure sharding mode for routers.
- **Container to Container Networking**: PCF Isolation Segment v1.11 supports container to container networking.
- **New Errand**: The PCF Isolation Segment v1.11 tile includes an errand that adds the isolation segment in the Cloud Controller Database. This changes how operators install the PCF Isolation Segment. For more information, see the [Installing PCF Isolation Segment](../opsguide/installing-pcf-is.html) topic.

For more information, see the [PCF Isolation Segment v1.11 Release Notes](../pcf-release-notes/segment-rn.html).

## <a id='cross'></a>Cross-platform Highlights

- **BOSH Backup and Restore (BBR)**: BBR is a command-line tool for backing up and restoring BOSH deployments. You can use it to back up and restore PCF components. BBR is a beta feature in PCF v1.11. For more information, see the [Backing Up Pivotal Cloud Foundry with BBR](../customizing/backup-restore/backup-pcf-bbr.html) and [Restoring Pivotal Cloud Foundry from Backup with BBR](../customizing/backup-restore/backup-pcf-bbr.html) topics.

## <a id='services'></a>Services Highlights

- **Scheduler for PCF**: 
- **PCF Metrics v1.4**: Simplifies tile installation, 
